# Database conventions

- Target DB: TheEyeBeta2025Live on 127.0.0.1:5432, schema "theeyebeta"
- Driver: psycopg3 (URL prefix postgresql+psycopg://)
- Every CREATE TABLE goes in schema "theeyebeta" — use op.create_table(..., schema=SCHEMA)
- Every raw op.execute uses fully-qualified theeyebeta.<table_name>
- Hypertable workflow: op.create_table(...) -> op.execute SELECT create_hypertable -> op.execute ALTER TABLE ... SET compression -> op.execute add_compression_policy
- All timestamps: timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now() where appropriate
- All FKs: ON DELETE RESTRICT unless documented otherwise
- Roles: tb_app (write), tb_rnd_readonly (read + INSERT proposals only)
- audit_log: tb_app gets INSERT + SELECT only; UPDATE and DELETE are revoked
- Every migration has a working downgrade() that reverses upgrade() in opposite order
- Every public.* reference is a bug — schema must always be theeyebeta
